premise_source_doc_sentence: Greenwich  (  -LSB- ˈɡrɛnɪtʃ -RSB- , -LSB- ˈɡrɪnɪdʒ -RSB- , -LSB- ˈɡrɪnɪtʃ -RSB- or -LSB- ˈɡrɛnɪdʒ -RSB-  )  is an early-established district of south east London , England , centred 5.5 miles  (  8.9 km  )  east south-east of Charing Cross .
Glen Johnson , a footballer who plays for England and Liverpool was born in Greenwich , 23 August 1984 .
The Royal Borough of Greenwich  (  -LSB- ˈɡrɛnɪtʃ -RSB- , -LSB- ˈɡrɪnɪdʒ -RSB- , -LSB- ˈɡrɪnɪtʃ -RSB- or -LSB- ˈɡrɛnɪdʒ -RSB-  )  is a London borough in south-east London , England .
